<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-685-285  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 685 285.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Nov 12 1990 v24 n46 p117(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Looking for Mr. Good Boss. (computer students list top tenindustry employers) (Computer Industry)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Kay, Sheryl.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A poll of 800 college students enrolled in computer sciences,information systems and electrical engineering studies at USuniversities finds that IBM heads a list of the top ten employersthey want to work for.andP;  The survey took into consideration suchfactors as opportunities for further training and education,responsibilities and corporate outlook in addition to such obviousfactors as pay and benefits.andP;  IBM, still regarded as the trendsetter for the industry, headed the list, followed by AT and T,with its global reputation for products and service.andP;  Otherleading firms were Hewlett Packard, appreciated as a team-orientedenvironment, DEC and Apple, both of which have a strong presencein the academic environment and General Electric.andP;  The top ten isrounded off by Motorola, Arthur Anderson/Anderson Consulting,Microsoft and Intel.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer industryCompaniesEmploymentSurveyStudentCareers.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   The top ten places students want to work. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>